# Swan Song deterministic controller replay, schema v1.
#
# Each non-comment line is: DECIMAL_SYSTEM_CYCLE FULL_CONTROLLER_STATE
# Controller names are the physical WonderSwan labels:
# x1,x2,x3,x4,y1,y2,y3,y4,start,a,b
# Use `none` to release every button. States replace rather than modify the
# preceding state, and gaps retain the most recently declared state.
#
# The clock is 36.864 MHz: 36,864 cycles = 1 ms and 3,686,400 cycles = 100 ms.
# Cycle 0 is the first cycle after reset release. An event at cycle N is visible
# before the rising edge recorded as trace cycle N.

# At 100 ms, hold the physical Start button.
3686400 start

# At 200 ms, release every button.
7372800 none

# At 300 ms, hold physical X2 and A together.
11059200 x2,a

# At 350 ms, replace that state with A only; X2 is released here.
12902400 a

# A script must end by releasing every button.
14745600 none
